CRICKET MATCH MANAGEMENT APPLICATION

UI/UX & FUNCTIONAL SPECIFICATION
(Ionic Angular Standalone + Tailwind CSS)

1. PROJECT OVERVIEW

The application is a professional cricket match management system designed for organizing, scoring, and tracking cricket matches and tournaments. It supports persistent storage of players, teams, matches, and tournaments, enabling data reuse across multiple events.

The primary goals are:

High usability with minimal cognitive load

Clear separation of concerns (Players, Teams, Matches, Tournaments)

Professional presentation suitable for official cricket organizations

Accurate, structured live scoring and match tracking

2. TECHNOLOGY & STRUCTURE REQUIREMENTS
Framework & Architecture

Ionic Angular using standalone components

Tailwind CSS for styling

Modular feature-based folder structure

Strict separation between UI components, services, and data models

Data Persistence

Local persistent database (IndexedDB or SQLite abstraction)

Centralized data access layer

All entities must be reusable across the application

Core Data Entities

Player

Team

Match

Tournament

MatchEvent (ball-by-ball data)

3. GLOBAL LAYOUT & RESPONSIVE BEHAVIOR
Header (All Screen Sizes)

Application name and logo

Current section title

Contextual indicators (e.g., live match in progress)

Access to settings

Navigation

Mobile and Tablet

Bottom navigation bar with primary sections:

Dashboard

Live Matches

Players

Teams

More (Tournaments, History)

Desktop and Wide Screens

Persistent left sidebar replacing the footer

Sidebar items:

Dashboard

Live Matches

Players

Teams

Tournaments

Match History

Settings

Navigation must be consistent and visible at all times.

4. DASHBOARD / HOME SCREEN

The dashboard is the primary overview and must present actionable information immediately.

Live Matches Section (Highest Priority)

Display currently running matches

Each match card includes:

Team A vs Team B

Current score (runs/wickets)

Overs

Batting team indicator

Cards must update dynamically

Selecting a card opens the live match scoring view

Upcoming Matches

Scheduled matches with date, time, teams, and venue

Quick Actions

Start New Match

Add Player

Create Team

Create Tournament

5. PLAYER MANAGEMENT
Player Creation
Required Fields

Full Name

Display Name (short name for scorecards)

Optional Fields (Collapsible Advanced Section)

Profile photo (fallback to initials avatar)

Player role (Batsman, Bowler, All-rounder, Wicketkeeper)

Batting style (Right-handed / Left-handed)

Bowling style (Fast, Medium, Spin)

Jersey number

Date of birth

Notes (injuries, remarks)

Player List View

Search and filter by role

Avatar, name, and role summary

Persistent storage for reuse

Player Profile View

Player details

Aggregated career statistics

Matches played

Teams associated with the player

6. TEAM MANAGEMENT
Team Creation

Team name

Team short code

Team logo (optional)

Home ground (optional)

Squad Management

Select players from existing player database

Ability to add new players inline

Assign leadership roles:

Captain

Vice-captain

Wicketkeeper

Team Detail Screen

Squad list

Team statistics

Past matches

Performance summary

7. MATCH CREATION FLOW

Match creation must be implemented as a guided, step-based process.

Step 1: Match Configuration

Match name

Match format (Friendly, League, Knockout)

Overs configuration:

Fixed overs

Unlimited overs

Step 2: Team Selection

Select two teams from saved teams

Option to create a new team inline

Step 3: Playing XI Selection

Select playing players from team squad

Validation rules:

Maximum players enforced

At least one wicketkeeper

Optional substitutes selection

Step 4: Match Metadata (Optional)

Venue

Umpire(s)

Scorer

8. TOSS MANAGEMENT

Toss screen must appear before match start

Simulated coin toss animation

Toss winner selection

Choice between batting or bowling

Automatic assignment of:

Batting team

Bowling team

Opening batsmen

Opening bowler

9. LIVE MATCH SCORING SYSTEM
Scoring Controls

Ball-by-ball scoring interface

Run options: 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 6

Extras:

No ball

Wide

Bye

Leg bye

Wicket Handling

Wicket type selection

Player dismissed

Incoming batsman selection

Over & Ball Management

Ball counter and over progression

Undo last ball functionality

Over summary display

Live Scoreboard

Team score

Overs completed

Current run rate

Batting player statistics

Bowler statistics

10. TOURNAMENT MANAGEMENT
Tournament Creation

Tournament name

Tournament format:

League

Knockout

Team selection

Points configuration

Tournament Dashboard

Points table

Match fixtures

Completed match results

Top performers

11. MATCH HISTORY & ANALYTICS
Match History

List of completed matches

Filters by date, team, and tournament

Match Summary

Full scorecard

Player performances

Result and match highlights

12. SETTINGS & ADMIN FEATURES

Theme configuration (dark mode default)

Data export (JSON format)

Reset demo data

Application information

13. USER EXPERIENCE PRINCIPLES

Progressive disclosure of advanced options

Clear labeling and hierarchy

No more than one primary action per screen

Consistent terminology across all sections

Zero ambiguity in match state transitions

14. ADDITIONAL PROFESSIONAL FEATURES

Auto-save on every scoring action

Resume match prompt on dashboard

Confirmation before ending or abandoning a match

Visual indicators for striker, non-striker, and current bowler

Audit-friendly ball-by-ball log

15. QUALITY EXPECTATIONS

No placeholder UI

No experimental or playful design elements

All screens must function logically even with partial data

UI must remain usable on low-resolution devices